// Zerodha algo trading: validate nested bracket expressions
// '(3+4)*[5-{2+1}]' → valid
// '(3+4]*[5-{2+1}]' → INVALID — mismatched types!

// Stack approach: O(n) O(n)
// For each char:
//   '(' '[' '{' → push
//   ')' → pop, must be '('
//   ']' → pop, must be '['
//   '}' → pop, must be '{'
//   empty stack at end → valid
```

concept_explanation.stack_java:
**Java Stack: use Deque, not legacy Stack class:**

```java
// WRONG: legacy Stack (synchronized, slow)
Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();

// CORRECT: ArrayDeque as stack (O(1) all ops, not synchronized)
Deque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
stack.push(1);       // addFirst — O(1)
stack.push(2);
stack.push(3);
stack.peek();        // peekFirst — O(1), doesn't remove
stack.pop();         // removeFirst — O(1), removes top
stack.isEmpty();     // O(1)
stack.size();        // O(1)

// LIFO: Last In, First Out
// push 1→2→3, pop gives 3→2→1
```

worked_example.final_code:
class MinStack {
    Deque<Integer> stack=new ArrayDeque<>(), minStack=new ArrayDeque<>();
    void push(int val){
        stack.push(val);
        if(minStack.isEmpty()||val<=minStack.peek()) minStack.push(val);
    }
    void pop(){
        if(stack.pop().equals(minStack.peek())) minStack.pop();
    }
    int top(){ return stack.peek(); }
    int getMin(){ return minStack.peek(); }
}
